value: Overarching notes were fine in B, B was louder overall, but frequency wise was fine.

A with bass not as much sub harmonic frequencies, snare a lot more plesant, slight sibilance. opposite - No bass compared to A, feels like 100Hz and below is gone, feel like kick is getting masked by the bass a lot, frequency of the kick attack is similar to bass pluck attack, EQ curve for vocals makes it sit better in the last section.
Lot more resonance in snare on opposite.
Felt very different. B had tighter lowend, but had some weird boosts in high-mids that felt like it was fighting the vocal, selected had a better relationship than A.
B seemed overall more boosted where needed to hear a difference/increase.

Selected sounds better than the last two, feels fuller around 400Hzish. Should have a better way of switching between comparing the A/B instantly between each other rather than having to stop and start kind of thing.
A sounded really good mix wise, but in second part it didn't sound as good. Keys in the mix at that part were too loud bot overall was the best sounding one.
Selected more balance, felt like there was a hole in the mids in the opposite one.
Slightly B. Mad how different parts can change in level just from EQ. Maybe B was a little tighter. Was difficult to pick.
